cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper proposes an algorithm that combines unsupervised representation learning and reinforcement learning of goal-conditioned policies for an autonomous agent to learn broadly applicable and general-purpose skill repertoires. The algorithm operates on raw image observations and goals for a real-world robotic system, which suggests that it belongs to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The use of reinforcement learning and unsupervised representation learning also suggests that it belongs to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on the efficiency and sample-efficiency of the algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
